**2.2: Add Smart Mapping for `replaceAllColumns`**

**Current (NAIVE):**
- Moves ALL tasks to first column (loses progress information)

**New (SMART):**
- Try to match tasks to new columns by **column title similarity**
- Example:
  - Old: "In Progress" → New: "In Progress" ✅ Perfect match
  - Old: "Review" → New: "Code Review" ✅ Similar match (contains "Review")
  - Old: "Custom Column" → New: First column ❌ No match → fallback

**Algorithm:**
```typescript
replaceAllColumns: (newColumns) => {
  const state = get();

  // Save undo entry...

  // Generate new columns with IDs
  const columns: KanbanColumn[] = newColumns.map((col, index) => ({
    ...col,
    id: `col-${Date.now()}-${index}`,
    order: index,
  }));

  // Smart mapping: Try to preserve task positions
  const tasks = state.tasks.map(task => {
    const oldColumn = state.columns.find(c => c.id === task.status);
    if (!oldColumn) return { ...task, status: columns[0].id as TaskStatus };

    // Try exact match first
    let newColumn = columns.find(c => c.title.toLowerCase() === oldColumn.title.toLowerCase());

    // If no exact match, try partial match (contains)
    if (!newColumn) {
      newColumn = columns.find(c =>
        c.title.toLowerCase().includes(oldColumn.title.toLowerCase()) ||
        oldColumn.title.toLowerCase().includes(c.title.toLowerCase())
      );
    }

    // Fallback: first column
    if (!newColumn) {
      newColumn = columns[0];
    }

    return { ...task, status: newColumn.id as TaskStatus };
  });

  set({ columns, tasks });
},
```

